# Bubble Sort - Complete Revision Notes

## 1. Definition

Bubble Sort is a simple comparison-based sorting algorithm.

It repeatedly compares adjacent elements and swaps them if they are in the wrong order.

After each pass, the largest unsorted element "bubbles up" to its correct position at the end of the array.

## 3. Algorithm

### Steps

1. Start from the first element.
2. Compare adjacent elements.
3. Swap if left element is greater than right element.
4. Continue until the end of the array.
5. Repeat for remaining unsorted elements.
6. Stop when no swaps occur in a pass.


## 5. Java Implementation (Basic)

```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class BubbleSort {

    public static void bubbleSort(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

            for (int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {

                if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {

                    int temp = arr[j];
                    arr[j] = arr[j + 1];
                    arr[j + 1] = temp;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {5, 1, 4, 2, 8};

        bubbleSort(arr);

        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
    }
}
```
## 6. Optimized Bubble Sort

### Idea

If no swaps occur in a pass, the array is already sorted.

Use a flag variable.

---

### Java Implementation

```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class BubbleSort {

    public static void bubbleSort(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

            boolean swapped = false;

            for (int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {

                if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {

                    int temp = arr[j];
                    arr[j] = arr[j + 1];
                    arr[j + 1] = temp;

                    swapped = true;
                }
            }

            if (!swapped) {
                break;
            }
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};

        bubbleSort(arr);

        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
    }
}




